                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13610",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=studio24",
                        "name": "studio24",
                        "displayName": "Simon R Jones",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Philip,\n\nCan you please try this script out (HostnameTestForm.php), you should access it via a web browser, and let me know if it works for you.\n\nI have managed to replicate your problem though cannot see why its occuring at present. With UTF-8 it seems mostly down to character encoding and that can be a little tricky to pin down. The form based version above should work fine for when accepting IDN hostnames via POST",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=studio24",
                        "name": "studio24",
                        "displayName": "Simon R Jones",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-22T04:13:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-22T04:13:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13612",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iezzip",
                        "name": "iezzip",
                        "displayName": "Philip Iezzi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks Simon. Check out your script at:\nhttp:\/\/web.onlime.ch\/HostnameTestForm.php\nIt won't work. I can't tell if my editor (joe under Debian Linux) messed up the encoding of your file. ZF is a \"clean\" checkout of r4172, no modified files there.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iezzip",
                        "name": "iezzip",
                        "displayName": "Philip Iezzi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-22T05:36:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-22T05:36:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13732",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=studio24",
                        "name": "studio24",
                        "displayName": "Simon R Jones",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Looks like the upload process messed up the character encoding. I'll put together some test scripts and give you a link to them soon so we can get to the bottom of this",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=studio24",
                        "name": "studio24",
                        "displayName": "Simon R Jones",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-27T12:25:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-27T12:25:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13733",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=studio24",
                        "name": "studio24",
                        "displayName": "Simon R Jones",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just a note that Alexander J\u00e4ger (lx at survive-linux dot com) has also reported this issue. I'll send him a link to test files too to help resolve this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=studio24",
                        "name": "studio24",
                        "displayName": "Simon R Jones",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-27T12:27:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-27T12:27:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14953",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iezzip",
                        "name": "iezzip",
                        "displayName": "Philip Iezzi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry about this bogus issue.\nThis was just a charset issue. My files were ISO-8859-1 encoded and I didn't apply utf8_encode() to the domain prior to passing it to the validator.\n\nsolution 1:\nFormat all your files to UTF-8\n\nsolution 2:\n$tld = utf8_encode('h\u00f6h\u00f6.ch');",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iezzip",
                        "name": "iezzip",
                        "displayName": "Philip Iezzi",
                        "active": true
                    },
